  "title": "Project Manager",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities</strong></u></p>\n<p>· Lead project team and facilitate their ability to complete the project on time</p>\n<p>· Manage and oversee the day-to-day management of projects and on-site works</p>\n<p>· Responsible for ensuring smooth implementation and monitoring of work progress.</p>\n<p>· Supervise workers and sub-contractors to ensure works are carried out as per schedule and in good quality</p>\n<p>· In charge of the planning, assessment and implementation of the whole project safety system and ISO system</p>\n<p>· Communicate and coordinate with clients and consultants, clarify requirement, plan, monitor and control the project, including carrying out implementation of the project.</p>\n<p>· Preparation of site progress report and necessary documentation and attend daily site meetings</p>\n<p>· Identify and resolve site issues effectively and efficiently.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<p>· Degree or Diploma in Electrical Engineering or its equivalent</p>\n<p>· Min 5 years relevant experience with at least 3 years project management experience at local projects</p>\n<p>· Strong technical abilities and interpersonal skills</p>\n<p>· Highly motivated and possess strong leadership qualities and the ability to work independently in a challenging environment.</p>\n<p>· Able to communicate effectively at all levels.</p>",
